2 HOUSE BILL 1204
1 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
2 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
3 Article – Education
4 SUBTITLE 11A. STUDENT ELOPEMENT FROM SCHOOL.
5 7–11A–01.
6 (A) IN THIS SUBTITLE THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
7 INDICATED.
8 (B) “BEHAVIOR INTERVENTION PLAN” HAS THE MEANING STATED IN §
9 7–1101 OF THIS TITLE.
10 (C) “ELOPEMENT” MEANS THE ACT OF A STUDENT LEAVING THE SCHOOL
11 CAMPUS WITHOUT THE PERMISSION OF A SCHOOL STAFF MEMBER WHO HAS
12 RESPONSIBILITY FOR THE STUDENT.
13 (D) “IEP” MEANS AN INDIVIDUALIZED EDUCATION PROGRAM AS DEFINED
14 UNDER THE FEDERAL INDIVIDUALS WITH DISABILITIES EDUCATION ACT.
15 (E) “NONPUBLIC SCHOOL” HAS THE MEANING STATED IN § 7–1101 OF THIS
16 TITLE.
17 (F) “SCHOOL” MEANS:
18 (1) A PUBLIC ELEMENTARY, MIDDLE, OR HIGH SCHOOL;
19 (2) THE MARYLAND SCHOOL FOR THE BLIND;
20 (3) THE MARYLAND SCHOOL FOR THE DEAF; AND
21 (4) A NONPUBLIC SCHOOL.
22 (G) “SCHOOL CAMPUS” MEANS THE BUILDINGS AND GROUNDS OF A
23 SCHOOL, INCLUDING A PLAYGROUND.
24 (H) (1) “WANDERING” MEANS THE ACT OF A STUDENT LEAVING A
25 CLASSROOM OR AREA ON THE SCHOOL CAMPUS, BUT NOT LEAVING THE SCHOOL
26 CAMPUS, WITHOUT THE PERMISSION OF A SCHOOL STAFF MEMBER WHO HAS
27 RESPONSIBILITY FOR THE STUDENT.
28 (2) “WANDERING” DOES NOT INCLUDE A STUDENT LEAVING A
29 CLASSROOM OR AREA ON THE SCHOOL CAMPUS UNDER A FLASH PASS OR ANOTHER

HOUSE BILL 1204 3
1 STANDING ARRANGEMENT THAT HAS BEEN APPROVED BY A SCHOOL
2 ADMINISTRATOR.
3 7–11A–02.
4 (A) EXCEPT AS PROVIDED IN SUBSECTION (B) OF THIS SECTION, EACH EACH
5 TIME A STUDENT ATTEMPTS OR ACCOMPLISHES AN ELOPEMENT, THE SCHOOL
6 SHALL NOTIFY THE STUDENT’S PARENT OR GUARDIAN WITHIN 24 HOURS OF THE
7 ELOPEMENT INCIDENT ON THE SAME DAY AS THE ELOPEMENT INCIDENT.
8 (B) (1) A SCHOOL IS NOT REQUIRED TO PROVIDE THE NOTICE UNDER
9 SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS SECTION TO THE PARENT OR GUARDIAN OF A STUDENT
10 WHO HAS AN IEP OR A BEHAVIOR INTERVENTION PLAN THAT INCLUDES MEASURES
11 FOR RESPONDING TO AN INCIDENT OF WANDERING OR ELOPEMENT BEHAVIOR BY
12 THE STUDENT.
13 (2) AT LEAST ONE TIME EACH YEAR, A SCHOOL OR A STUDENT’S IEP
14 TEAM SHALL REVIEW AND ADDRESS WITH RELEVANT STAKEHOLDERS A STUDENT’S
15 WANDERING OR ELOPEMENT BEHAVIOR IN UPDATING THE STUDENT’S IEP OR
16 BEHAVIOR INTERVENTION PLAN.
17 7–11A–03.
18 (A) ON OR BEFORE AUGUST 1, 2026, AND EACH AUGUST 1 THEREAFTER,
19 EACH PUBLIC SCHOOL SHALL SUBMIT TO THE COUNTY BOARD A REPORT FOR THE
20 PRIOR SCHOOL YEAR ON:
21 (1) THE NUMBER OF ELOPEMENT INCIDENTS, DISAGGREGATED BY
22 JURISDICTION, DISABILITY, RACE, GENDER, AGE, AND TYPE OF PLACEMENT;
23 (2) THE NUMBER OF ELOPEMENT INCIDENTS FOR EACH STUDENT
24 WHO HAD AT LEAST ONE ELOPEMENT INCIDENT, DISAGGREGATED BY
25 JURISDICTION, DISABILITY, RACE, GENDER, AGE, AND TYPE OF PLACEMENT; AND
26 (3) THE STEPS TAKEN BY THE SCHOOL TO REDUCE THE NUMBER OF
27 ELOPEMENT INCIDENTS AND TO ENCOURAGE POSITIVE BEHAVIORAL
28 INTERVENTIONS, INCLUDING A DESCRIPTION OF:
29 (I) THE PROFESSIONAL DEVELOPMENT PROVIDED TO
30 DESIGNATED SCHOOL PERSONNEL ON IDENTIFICATION OF WANDERING OR
31 ELOPEMENT BEHAVIOR IN STUDENTS, INCLUDING ANTECEDENTS TO WANDERING
32 OR ELOPEMENT BEHAVIOR, AND POSITIVE BEHAVIORAL INTERVENTIONS USED TO
33 ADDRESS WANDERING AND ELOPEMENT BEHAVIOR; AND

4 HOUSE BILL 1204
1 (II) THE POLICY CHANGES MADE OR NEW PROFESSIONAL
2 DEVELOPMENT OPPORTUNITIES OFFERED THAT WERE DESIGNED TO PROMOTE
3 POSITIVE BEHAVIORAL INTERVENTIONS AND REDUCE INCIDENTS OF WANDERING
4 AND ELOPEMENT BEHAVIORS IN THE UPCOMING SCHOOL YEAR.
5 (B) (1) A COUNTY BOARD SHALL VERIFY THE ACCURACY OF A REPORT
6 FROM A SCHOOL THAT REPORTS ZERO ELOPEMENT INCIDENTS UNDER SUBSECTION
7 (A) OF THIS SECTION.
8 (2) IF A COUNTY BOARD IS UNABLE TO VERIFY THE ACCURACY OF A
9 REPORT SUBMITTED BY A SCHOOL UNDER SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS SECTION, THE
10 COUNTY BOARD SHALL MAKE RECOMMENDATIONS TO THE SCHOOL FOR
11 IMPROVEMENTS IN DATA COLLECTION AND POSITIVE BEHAVIORAL INTERVENTIONS
12 AT THE SCHOOL.
13 (C) ON OR BEFORE OCTOBER 1, 2026, AND EACH OCTOBER 1 THEREAFTER,
14 EACH COUNTY BOARD SHALL SUBMIT TO THE DEPARTMENT A REPORT THAT
15 COMPILES THE INFORMATION REPORTED UNDER SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS SECTION.
